Package org.sureassert.uc.annotation

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Exemplar
    Identifies a method that should be tested and specifies test data and optionally stubs and/or an expected result.
    Exemplars
    Allows multiple Exemplars to be defined.
    HasJUnit
    Demarks a JUnit test class for a class.
    IgnoreTestCoverage
    Prevents Sureassert UC gathering or reporting any test coverage data for the annotated class, method or constructor.
    MultiUseCase
    Allows multiple use-cases to be defined.
    NamedClass
    Assigns a name to a class.
    NamedInstance
    Assigns a name to the instance returned by a field, or if specified on a class assigns a name to the instance returned by the default constructor.
    NoAutoRun
    Prevents Sureassert UC running any JUnit tests on the annotated class automatically.
    SINType
    Identifies a method that can be used as a SIN Type within SIN expressions.
    Stubs
    Identifies stubs to apply when running the annotated JUnit test method.
    TestDouble
    Demarks a class as a test-double for a stated class.
    TestState
    Specifies values to be set on a field in the use case execution context, before UseCases are run on the class.
    UseCase
    Identifies a method that should be tested and specifies test data and optionally stubs and/or an expected result.
